# Asset Bridge Project

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 with App Router
- Supabase (Auth, Database, Storage)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS

## Key Directories
- `src/app/api/` - API routes
- `src/components/` - React components
- `src/contexts/` - React contexts (auth-context)
- `src/lib/supabase/` - Supabase client utilities

## Database Tables
- `assets` - Main table for logos/icons
  - `component_name` - Unique name for the asset
  - `user_id` - Owner (null for anonymous)
  - `visibility` - "public" or "private"
  - `svg_url`, `original_url`, `react_component`

## Important Patterns
- Use service role key for admin operations (bypasses RLS)
- Assets created without login have `user_id = null`
- Local dev uses different DB than production

## Admin Users
- Check `src/lib/admin.ts` for admin email list
